The paper deals with a sparse signal recovery problem using Bayesian learning, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Additionally, the proposed algorithm involves an expectation-maximization framework, which is commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI).
